Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.03,0:00:05.26,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Titanic had enough\Nlifeboats to satisfy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.26,0:00:06.49,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.49,0:00:07.71,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,That sentence sounds safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.57,0:00:11.34,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,In 1912, it was the\Nproblem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.62,0:00:14.56,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,British rules measured\Nlifeboats by
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.56,0:00:16.27,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,tonnage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.27,0:00:17.99,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Above 10,000 tons, the top
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.99,0:00:21.36,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,bracket required sixteen\Nlifeboats for 990
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.36,0:00:23.34,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:25.32,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Titanic carried sixteen\Nlifeboats
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.32,0:00:28.52,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,and four collapsibles,\Nenough for about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.52,0:00:30.78,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,1,176 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.78,0:00:33.04,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,More than 2,200 were\Naboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.04,0:00:34.58,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The paperwork said\Ncompliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:36.36,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The ship said otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.16,0:00:38.53,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Some boats left\Nunderfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.19,0:00:40.23,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The law failed one way;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.83,0:00:42.31,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,evacuation failed another.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.31,0:00:43.80,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Afterward,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.80,0:00:46.54,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,investigators pushed the\Ncorrection: count
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.54,0:00:48.30,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,people carried, not\Ntonnage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.35,0:00:51.67,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Two years later, SOLAS\Nturned that lesson
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.67,0:00:53.19,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,into international\Nrulemaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.19,0:00:54.71,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,The old
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.71,0:00:56.67,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,category kept measuring\Nyesterday's ship
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.67,0:00:58.18,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,while approving tomorrow's\Nrisk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.98,0:01:02.35,DocumentaryLowerThird,,0,0,0,,Small causes, massive\Nconsequences.
